{"author":{"id":"5e53c9bce7eeb69e347743575f6133426338c29498e200aa8bf1bef46209d02a"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1586531580,"nonce":"8V105RkNGtLdUs+TS4jhtaaQ8Qc=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU1OTc5MzkyOTc=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2964","origin":"github"},"title":"gatk2_mutect2 always fails if $_JAVA_OPTIONS is set","message":"[This construct](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/fc3deb5bce07a12b7f9bbd380118a7d2230a1003/tools/gatk4/macros.xml#L21) always results in a tool failure if `$_JAVA_OPTIONS` is set, since `[[ -z $_JAVA_OPTIONS ]]` evaluates `false` and skips the rest of the `\u0026\u0026`'d commands.\n\n```console\nln -s /galaxy/files/001/dataset_1.dat input.bam \u0026\u0026 samtools index input.bam \\\n    \u0026\u0026 [[ -z $_JAVA_OPTIONS ]] \u0026\u0026 export JAVA_OPTS=$_JAVA_OPTIONS \\\n    \u0026\u0026 gatk GetSampleName --input=\"input.bam\" --output=\"samplename.txt\" \\\n    \u0026\u0026 sample=`cat samplename.txt` \u0026\u0026 [[ -z $_JAVA_OPTIONS ]] \\\n    \u0026\u0026 export JAVA_OPTS=$_JAVA_OPTIONS \u0026\u0026 \\\n    gatk Mutect2 --QUIET --tumor-sample $sample --input input.bam --output output.vcf.gz\n```\n\nAlso, correct me if I'm wrong, but `$sample` seems unsafe here. `gatk GetSampleName` reads the `SM` field from `RG`, which in my testing, can contain anything.","files":null}]}